commit.message:
Add 2.6 back to versions list in README

Fixes #63
Note flicker of python2.6 support in 0.14.0
Add back Python 2.6 support
Use Travis CI container builds
Add pypy to setup classifiers
Make tests pass under PyPy3
Add Python 3.5 support
Test the README example and make it Python 3 compatible
Fix some broken tests using assertTrue incorrectly

Get tests passing under Python 3

Currently, we pass through the Python 3 csv module. Unfortunately,
Python 3's csv module has a fairly significantly different API, and is
not compatible with even the API given in the README. This gets the
tests passing under Python 3.3 and 3.4, and doesn't break Python 2.6,
2.7, or pypy.
Bump version to 0.14.1
Manually revert c0b7655, #39
A bit more explicit about file open mode
Clarify version support
Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/master' into issue39
Clarify bytestring expectation
Bump version to 0.13.0

Merge pull request #56 from ryanhiebert/tox2

Fix install under Tox 2

Drop support for Python 3.2

Remove Python 2.5 from classifiers since it's not tested.

Use tox-travis for CI

Remove cruft from tox.ini, and update with all tested versions. Update
.travis.yml to use tox-travis, and use tox to run the tests. Add Python
3.2, 3.3, and 3.4 classifiers to setup.py.
Explicitly declare the encoding of README.rst
Handle empty CSV under DictReader
PEP8 cleanup

Defer to stdlib if under python 3

Also bump to 0.12.0

DictWriter.writeheader should defer to the underlying writer

d27d182 sought to DRY .writeheaders a bit, but introduced a bug.
No diff is too simple for a test, apparently.
Bump version

Handle decimals (and other numbers) correctly under QUOTE_NONNUMERIC

Thanks to @adlh in #41 for the report, and @kengruven  for pointing
out the numbers module, new in py 2.6

Merge pull request #37 from pombredanne/patch-1

Fixed inconsistent indentation

Merge pull request #44 from svisser/patch-1

Updated method to use local variable instead of instance variable

Merge pull request #47 from kengruven/master

Only call isinstance(value, float) if needed.
